  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

Name:          Tim Berners-Lee
Lived:         1955 - present
Nationality:   English
Field:         Computing
Known For:     World Wide Web
Contribution:  Invented the Web in 1989; gave it to the world for free
Quote:         "The web does not just connect machines, it connects people."

Name:          Abraham Lincoln
Lived:         1809 - 1865
Nationality:   American
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Emancipation Proclamation
Contribution:  16th US President; preserved Union; abolished slavery; Gettysburg Address
Quote:         "Government of the people, by the people, for the people."

============================================================
  ARTIFICIAL INTELLIGENCE & MACHINE LEARNING
============================================================

Concept:     LSTM
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Gating mechanisms solve vanishing gradient in sequences
Year:        1997
Researchers: Hochreiter/Schmidhuber
Applications:NLP, speech, time series
Related:     GRU, RNN, gates, cell state

Concept:     CNN
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Convolutional filters detect spatial features hierarchically
Year:        1989
Researchers: LeCun et al.
Applications:Image classification, object detection
Related:     Pooling, feature maps, ResNet

Concept:     RAG
Category:    Architecture
Definition:  Combines retrieval from knowledge base with generative model
Year:        2020
Researchers: Lewis et al.
Applications:QA, chatbots, enterprise AI
Related:     Vector database, semantic search, LLM

